\title{Histolab}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Digital pathology image processing toolkit for whole slide images (WSI). Use this skill when working with histopathology slides, processing H&E or IHC stained tissue images, extracting tiles from gigapixel pathology images, detecting tissue regions, segmenting tissue masks, or preparing datasets for computational pathology deep learning pipelines. Applies to WSI formats (SVS, TIFF, NDPI), tile-based analysis, and histological image preprocessing workflows.}

\subtree{
\title{Histolab}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Histolab is a Python library for processing whole slide images (WSI) in digital pathology. It automates tissue detection, extracts informative tiles from gigapixel images, and prepares datasets for deep learning pipelines. The library handles multiple WSI formats, implements sophisticated tissue segmentation, and provides flexible tile extraction strategies.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Installation}
\pre{\startverb
uv pip install histolab
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start}
\p{Basic workflow for extracting tiles from a whole slide image:}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.slide import Slide
from histolab.tiler import RandomTiler

# Load slide
slide = Slide("slide.svs", processed_path="output/")

# Configure tiler
tiler = RandomTiler(
    tile_size=(512, 512),
    n_tiles=100,
    level=0,
    seed=42
)

# Preview tile locations
tiler.locate_tiles(slide, n_tiles=20)

# Extract tiles
tiler.extract(slide)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Capabilities}
\subtree{
\title{1. Slide Management}
\p{Load, inspect, and work with whole slide images in various formats.}

\p{\strong{Common operations:}}

\ul{
\li{Loading WSI files (SVS, TIFF, NDPI, etc.)}
\li{Accessing slide metadata (dimensions, magnification, properties)}
\li{Generating thumbnails for visualization}
\li{Working with pyramidal image structures}
\li{Extracting regions at specific coordinates}
}

\p{\strong{Key classes:} \code{\startverb Slide\stopverb}}

\p{\strong{Reference:} \code{\startverb references/slide_management.md\stopverb} contains comprehensive documentation on:}

\ul{
\li{Slide initialization and configuration}
\li{Built-in sample datasets (prostate, ovarian, breast, heart, kidney tissues)}
\li{Accessing slide properties and metadata}
\li{Thumbnail generation and visualization}
\li{Working with pyramid levels}
\li{Multi-slide processing workflows}
}

\p{\strong{Example workflow:}}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.slide import Slide
from histolab.data import prostate_tissue

# Load sample data
prostate_svs, prostate_path = prostate_tissue()

# Initialize slide
slide = Slide(prostate_path, processed_path="output/")

# Inspect properties
print(f"Dimensions: {slide.dimensions}")
print(f"Levels: {slide.levels}")
print(f"Magnification: {slide.properties.get('openslide.objective-power')}")

# Save thumbnail
slide.save_thumbnail()
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Tissue Detection and Masks}
\p{Automatically identify tissue regions and filter background/artifacts.}

\p{\strong{Common operations:}}

\ul{
\li{Creating binary tissue masks}
\li{Detecting largest tissue region}
\li{Excluding background and artifacts}
\li{Custom tissue segmentation}
\li{Removing pen annotations}
}

\p{\strong{Key classes:} \code{\startverb TissueMask\stopverb}, \code{\startverb BiggestTissueBoxMask\stopverb}, \code{\startverb BinaryMask\stopverb}}

\p{\strong{Reference:} \code{\startverb references/tissue_masks.md\stopverb} contains comprehensive documentation on:}

\ul{
\li{TissueMask: Segments all tissue regions using automated filters}
\li{BiggestTissueBoxMask: Returns bounding box of largest tissue region (default)}
\li{BinaryMask: Base class for custom mask implementations}
\li{Visualizing masks with \code{\startverb locate_mask()\stopverb}}
\li{Creating custom rectangular and annotation-exclusion masks}
\li{Mask integration with tile extraction}
\li{Best practices and troubleshooting}
}

\p{\strong{Example workflow:}}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.masks import TissueMask, BiggestTissueBoxMask

# Create tissue mask for all tissue regions
tissue_mask = TissueMask()

# Visualize mask on slide
slide.locate_mask(tissue_mask)

# Get mask array
mask_array = tissue_mask(slide)

# Use largest tissue region (default for most extractors)
biggest_mask = BiggestTissueBoxMask()
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{When to use each mask:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb TissueMask\stopverb}: Multiple tissue sections, comprehensive analysis}
\li{\code{\startverb BiggestTissueBoxMask\stopverb}: Single main tissue section, exclude artifacts (default)}
\li{Custom \code{\startverb BinaryMask\stopverb}: Specific ROI, exclude annotations, custom segmentation}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Tile Extraction}
\p{Extract smaller regions from large WSI using different strategies.}

\p{\strong{Three extraction strategies:}}

\p{\strong{RandomTiler:} Extract fixed number of randomly positioned tiles}

\ul{
\li{Best for: Sampling diverse regions, exploratory analysis, training data}
\li{Key parameters: \code{\startverb n_tiles\stopverb}, \code{\startverb seed\stopverb} for reproducibility}
}

\p{\strong{GridTiler:} Systematically extract tiles across tissue in grid pattern}

\ul{
\li{Best for: Complete coverage, spatial analysis, reconstruction}
\li{Key parameters: \code{\startverb pixel_overlap\stopverb} for sliding windows}
}

\p{\strong{ScoreTiler:} Extract top-ranked tiles based on scoring functions}

\ul{
\li{Best for: Most informative regions, quality-driven selection}
\li{Key parameters: \code{\startverb scorer\stopverb} (NucleiScorer, CellularityScorer, custom)}
}

\p{\strong{Common parameters:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb tile_size\stopverb}: Tile dimensions (e.g., (512, 512))}
\li{\code{\startverb level\stopverb}: Pyramid level for extraction (0 = highest resolution)}
\li{\code{\startverb check_tissue\stopverb}: Filter tiles by tissue content}
\li{\code{\startverb tissue_percent\stopverb}: Minimum tissue coverage (default 80\%)}
\li{\code{\startverb extraction_mask\stopverb}: Mask defining extraction region}
}

\p{\strong{Reference:} \code{\startverb references/tile_extraction.md\stopverb} contains comprehensive documentation on:}

\ul{
\li{Detailed explanation of each tiler strategy}
\li{Available scorers (NucleiScorer, CellularityScorer, custom)}
\li{Tile preview with \code{\startverb locate_tiles()\stopverb}}
\li{Extraction workflows and reporting}
\li{Advanced patterns (multi-level, hierarchical extraction)}
\li{Performance optimization and troubleshooting}
}

\p{\strong{Example workflows:}}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.tiler import RandomTiler, GridTiler, ScoreTiler
from histolab.scorer import NucleiScorer

# Random sampling (fast, diverse)
random_tiler = RandomTiler(
    tile_size=(512, 512),
    n_tiles=100,
    level=0,
    seed=42,
    check_tissue=True,
    tissue_percent=80.0
)
random_tiler.extract(slide)

# Grid coverage (comprehensive)
grid_tiler = GridTiler(
    tile_size=(512, 512),
    level=0,
    pixel_overlap=0,
    check_tissue=True
)
grid_tiler.extract(slide)

# Score-based selection (most informative)
score_tiler = ScoreTiler(
    tile_size=(512, 512),
    n_tiles=50,
    scorer=NucleiScorer(),
    level=0
)
score_tiler.extract(slide, report_path="tiles_report.csv")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Always preview before extracting:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Preview tile locations on thumbnail
tiler.locate_tiles(slide, n_tiles=20)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Filters and Preprocessing}
\p{Apply image processing filters for tissue detection, quality control, and preprocessing.}

\p{\strong{Filter categories:}}

\p{\strong{Image Filters:} Color space conversions, thresholding, contrast enhancement}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb RgbToGrayscale\stopverb}, \code{\startverb RgbToHsv\stopverb}, \code{\startverb RgbToHed\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb OtsuThreshold\stopverb}, \code{\startverb AdaptiveThreshold\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb StretchContrast\stopverb}, \code{\startverb HistogramEqualization\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Morphological Filters:} Structural operations on binary images}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb BinaryDilation\stopverb}, \code{\startverb BinaryErosion\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb BinaryOpening\stopverb}, \code{\startverb BinaryClosing\stopverb}}
\li{\code{\startverb RemoveSmallObjects\stopverb}, \code{\startverb RemoveSmallHoles\stopverb}}
}

\p{\strong{Composition:} Chain multiple filters together}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb Compose\stopverb}: Create filter pipelines}
}

\p{\strong{Reference:} \code{\startverb references/filters_preprocessing.md\stopverb} contains comprehensive documentation on:}

\ul{
\li{Detailed explanation of each filter type}
\li{Filter composition and chaining}
\li{Common preprocessing pipelines (tissue detection, pen removal, nuclei enhancement)}
\li{Applying filters to tiles}
\li{Custom mask filters}
\li{Quality control filters (blur detection, tissue coverage)}
\li{Best practices and troubleshooting}
}

\p{\strong{Example workflows:}}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.filters.compositions import Compose
from histolab.filters.image_filters import RgbToGrayscale, OtsuThreshold
from histolab.filters.morphological_filters import (
    BinaryDilation, RemoveSmallHoles, RemoveSmallObjects
)

# Standard tissue detection pipeline
tissue_detection = Compose([
    RgbToGrayscale(),
    OtsuThreshold(),
    BinaryDilation(disk_size=5),
    RemoveSmallHoles(area_threshold=1000),
    RemoveSmallObjects(area_threshold=500)
])

# Use with custom mask
from histolab.masks import TissueMask
custom_mask = TissueMask(filters=tissue_detection)

# Apply filters to tile
from histolab.tile import Tile
filtered_tile = tile.apply_filters(tissue_detection)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Visualization}
\p{Visualize slides, masks, tile locations, and extraction quality.}

\p{\strong{Common visualization tasks:}}

\ul{
\li{Displaying slide thumbnails}
\li{Visualizing tissue masks}
\li{Previewing tile locations}
\li{Assessing tile quality}
\li{Creating reports and figures}
}

\p{\strong{Reference:} \code{\startverb references/visualization.md\stopverb} contains comprehensive documentation on:}

\ul{
\li{Slide thumbnail display and saving}
\li{Mask visualization with \code{\startverb locate_mask()\stopverb}}
\li{Tile location preview with \code{\startverb locate_tiles()\stopverb}}
\li{Displaying extracted tiles and mosaics}
\li{Quality assessment (score distributions, top vs bottom tiles)}
\li{Multi-slide visualization}
\li{Filter effect visualization}
\li{Exporting high-resolution figures and PDF reports}
\li{Interactive visualization in Jupyter notebooks}
}

\p{\strong{Example workflows:}}

\pre{\startverb
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from histolab.masks import TissueMask

# Display slide thumbnail
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
plt.imshow(slide.thumbnail)
plt.title(f"Slide: {slide.name}")
plt.axis('off')
plt.show()

# Visualize tissue mask
tissue_mask = TissueMask()
slide.locate_mask(tissue_mask)

# Preview tile locations
tiler = RandomTiler(tile_size=(512, 512), n_tiles=50)
tiler.locate_tiles(slide, n_tiles=20)

# Display extracted tiles in grid
from pathlib import Path
from PIL import Image

tile_paths = list(Path("output/tiles/").glob("*.png"))[:16]
fig, axes = plt.subplots(4, 4, figsize=(12, 12))
axes = axes.ravel()

for idx, tile_path in enumerate(tile_paths):
    tile_img = Image.open(tile_path)
    axes[idx].imshow(tile_img)
    axes[idx].set_title(tile_path.stem, fontsize=8)
    axes[idx].axis('off')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Typical Workflows}
\subtree{
\title{Workflow 1: Exploratory Tile Extraction}
\p{Quick sampling of diverse tissue regions for initial analysis.}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.slide import Slide
from histolab.tiler import RandomTiler
import logging

# Enable logging for progress tracking
logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)

# Load slide
slide = Slide("slide.svs", processed_path="output/random_tiles/")

# Inspect slide
print(f"Dimensions: {slide.dimensions}")
print(f"Levels: {slide.levels}")
slide.save_thumbnail()

# Configure random tiler
random_tiler = RandomTiler(
    tile_size=(512, 512),
    n_tiles=100,
    level=0,
    seed=42,
    check_tissue=True,
    tissue_percent=80.0
)

# Preview locations
random_tiler.locate_tiles(slide, n_tiles=20)

# Extract tiles
random_tiler.extract(slide)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow 2: Comprehensive Grid Extraction}
\p{Complete tissue coverage for whole-slide analysis.}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.slide import Slide
from histolab.tiler import GridTiler
from histolab.masks import TissueMask

# Load slide
slide = Slide("slide.svs", processed_path="output/grid_tiles/")

# Use TissueMask for all tissue sections
tissue_mask = TissueMask()
slide.locate_mask(tissue_mask)

# Configure grid tiler
grid_tiler = GridTiler(
    tile_size=(512, 512),
    level=1,  # Use level 1 for faster extraction
    pixel_overlap=0,
    check_tissue=True,
    tissue_percent=70.0
)

# Preview grid
grid_tiler.locate_tiles(slide)

# Extract all tiles
grid_tiler.extract(slide, extraction_mask=tissue_mask)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow 3: Quality-Driven Tile Selection}
\p{Extract most informative tiles based on nuclei density.}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.slide import Slide
from histolab.tiler import ScoreTiler
from histolab.scorer import NucleiScorer
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load slide
slide = Slide("slide.svs", processed_path="output/scored_tiles/")

# Configure score tiler
score_tiler = ScoreTiler(
    tile_size=(512, 512),
    n_tiles=50,
    level=0,
    scorer=NucleiScorer(),
    check_tissue=True
)

# Preview top tiles
score_tiler.locate_tiles(slide, n_tiles=15)

# Extract with report
score_tiler.extract(slide, report_path="tiles_report.csv")

# Analyze scores
report_df = pd.read_csv("tiles_report.csv")
plt.hist(report_df['score'], bins=20, edgecolor='black')
plt.xlabel('Tile Score')
plt.ylabel('Frequency')
plt.title('Distribution of Tile Scores')
plt.show()
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow 4: Multi-Slide Processing Pipeline}
\p{Process entire slide collection with consistent parameters.}

\pre{\startverb
from pathlib import Path
from histolab.slide import Slide
from histolab.tiler import RandomTiler
import logging

logging.basicConfig(level=logging.INFO)

# Configure tiler once
tiler = RandomTiler(
    tile_size=(512, 512),
    n_tiles=50,
    level=0,
    seed=42,
    check_tissue=True
)

# Process all slides
slide_dir = Path("slides/")
output_base = Path("output/")

for slide_path in slide_dir.glob("*.svs"):
    print(f"\nProcessing: {slide_path.name}")

    # Create slide-specific output directory
    output_dir = output_base / slide_path.stem
    output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

    # Load and process slide
    slide = Slide(slide_path, processed_path=output_dir)

    # Save thumbnail for review
    slide.save_thumbnail()

    # Extract tiles
    tiler.extract(slide)

    print(f"Completed: {slide_path.name}")
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow 5: Custom Tissue Detection and Filtering}
\p{Handle slides with artifacts, annotations, or unusual staining.}

\pre{\startverb
from histolab.slide import Slide
from histolab.masks import TissueMask
from histolab.tiler import RandomTiler
from histolab.filters.compositions import Compose
from histolab.filters.image_filters import RgbToGrayscale, OtsuThreshold
from histolab.filters.morphological_filters import (
    BinaryDilation, RemoveSmallObjects, RemoveSmallHoles
)

# Define custom filter pipeline for aggressive artifact removal
aggressive_filters = Compose([
    RgbToGrayscale(),
    OtsuThreshold(),
    BinaryDilation(disk_size=10),
    RemoveSmallHoles(area_threshold=5000),
    RemoveSmallObjects(area_threshold=3000)  # Remove larger artifacts
])

# Create custom mask
custom_mask = TissueMask(filters=aggressive_filters)

# Load slide and visualize mask
slide = Slide("slide.svs", processed_path="output/")
slide.locate_mask(custom_mask)

# Extract with custom mask
tiler = RandomTiler(tile_size=(512, 512), n_tiles=100)
tiler.extract(slide, extraction_mask=custom_mask)
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices}
\subtree{
\title{Slide Loading and Inspection}
\ol{
\li{Always inspect slide properties before processing}
\li{Save thumbnails for quick visual review}
\li{Check pyramid levels and dimensions}
\li{Verify tissue is present using thumbnails}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tissue Detection}
\ol{
\li{Preview masks with \code{\startverb locate_mask()\stopverb} before extraction}
\li{Use \code{\startverb TissueMask\stopverb} for multiple sections, \code{\startverb BiggestTissueBoxMask\stopverb} for single sections}
\li{Customize filters for specific stains (H&E vs IHC)}
\li{Handle pen annotations with custom masks}
\li{Test masks on diverse slides}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tile Extraction}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Always preview with \code{\startverb locate_tiles()\stopverb} before extracting}}
\li{Choose appropriate tiler:}
\li{RandomTiler: Sampling and exploration}
\li{GridTiler: Complete coverage}
\li{ScoreTiler: Quality-driven selection}
\li{Set appropriate \code{\startverb tissue_percent\stopverb} threshold (70-90\% typical)}
\li{Use seeds for reproducibility in RandomTiler}
\li{Extract at appropriate pyramid level for analysis resolution}
\li{Enable logging for large datasets}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Performance}
\ol{
\li{Extract at lower levels (1, 2) for faster processing}
\li{Use \code{\startverb BiggestTissueBoxMask\stopverb} over \code{\startverb TissueMask\stopverb} when appropriate}
\li{Adjust \code{\startverb tissue_percent\stopverb} to reduce invalid tile attempts}
\li{Limit \code{\startverb n_tiles\stopverb} for initial exploration}
\li{Use \code{\startverb pixel_overlap=0\stopverb} for non-overlapping grids}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quality Control}
\ol{
\li{Validate tile quality (check for blur, artifacts, focus)}
\li{Review score distributions for ScoreTiler}
\li{Inspect top and bottom scoring tiles}
\li{Monitor tissue coverage statistics}
\li{Filter extracted tiles by additional quality metrics if needed}
}
}
}

